<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1054" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1054">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Department of Defense Files</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Truman</persName> to
                                the British Prime Minister</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Churchill</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-29">April 29,
                                1945</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>17. Replying to your Number 19, the Combined Chiefs of Staff in F.A.N.
                            536, on 28 April, with my approval, authorized Alexander to accomplish
                            what I understand to be your idea regarding Trieste and other areas
                            formerly under Italian rule as a matter of military necessity.</p>
                        <p>I do not know what the effect of the forthcoming German surrender in
                            Italy may have on Alexander’s plans in this matter.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>